We brainstormed a few alternatives:

## Alternative 1

Enhance existing annotation:

```java
public @interface DisabledOnOs {
	OS[] value() default {};
	String[] architectures() default {};
}
@DisabledOnOs(architectures = "aarch64") // OS is not checked anymore
@DisabledOnOs(architectures = {"aarch64", "x86_64"}) // OS is not checked anymore
@DisabledOnOs(value = OS.LINUX, architectures = {"aarch64", "x86_64"})
```

Or introduce `OS.ANY` instead of using `{}`.

## Alternative 2

Define new annotation:
```java
public @interface DisabledOnArchitecture {
	String[] value();
	OS[] os() default {};
}
@DisabledOnArchitecture("aarch64") // OS is not checked
@DisabledOnArchitecture({"aarch64", "x86_64"}) // OS is not checked
@DisabledOnArchitecture(value = {"aarch64", "x86_64"}, os = OS.LINUX)
```

## Alternative 3

Recommend using `@DisabledIf`

```java
@DisabledIf("linuxAarch64")
@Test
void test() {}

static boolean linuxAarch64() {
	return OS.current() == OS.LINUX && "aarch64".equals(System.getProperty("os.arch"))
}
```
